The mother is devastated.

265
00:11:33,366 --> 00:11:34,966
The father is furious.

266
00:11:34,968 --> 00:11:36,300
I would be, too.

267
00:11:36,302 --> 00:11:38,102
LIM: Shaun is a resident.

268
00:11:38,104 --> 00:11:39,670
Residents make mistakes.

269
00:11:40,774 --> 00:11:42,807
Managing these parents'
emotional concerns

270
00:11:42,809 --> 00:11:45,609
is as much a part of this job
as operating on their daughter.

271
00:11:45,611 --> 00:11:48,012
[SIGHS] Social cues are hard for Shaun,

272
00:11:48,014 --> 00:11:49,413
but we've been working with him...

273
00:11:49,415 --> 00:11:51,415
You should be focused
on your own shortcomings,

274
00:11:51,417 --> 00:11:54,322
like retaining the formula
for vascular impedance.

275
00:11:55,054 --> 00:11:56,420
Dr. Han.

276
00:11:56,422 --> 00:11:59,157
♪♪

277
00:11:59,159 --> 00:12:01,793
We could patch each
individual hole in the heart

278
00:12:01,795 --> 00:12:03,661
if we cut open the ventricle...

279
00:12:03,663 --> 00:12:05,328
Don't change the subject, Dr. Murphy.

280
00:12:05,330 --> 00:12:06,830
I didn't, Dr. Han.

281
00:12:06,832 --> 00:12:09,232
We were talking about the baby.

282
00:12:09,234 --> 00:12:10,713
Really?

283
00:12:11,503 --> 00:12:13,770
You don't see a difference
in the nature of your discussion

284
00:12:13,772 --> 00:12:15,705
before I arrived and after?

285
00:12:17,375 --> 00:12:21,111
We<i> were</i> talking about the baby.

286
00:12:21,113 --> 00:12:24,514
♪♪

287
00:12:26,618 --> 00:12:29,452
They tried the approach you
suggested at L.A. Children's.

288
00:12:29,454 --> 00:12:31,288
The baby died a week later.

289
00:12:31,290 --> 00:12:34,691
The suture line didn't hold,
and the cardiac wall ruptured.

290
00:12:34,693 --> 00:12:35,758
Keep looking.

291
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:37,994
Dr. Murphy,

292
00:12:37,996 --> 00:12:40,743
do not talk with those parents again.

293
00:12:44,368 --> 00:12:45,767
I'll walk with you.

294
00:12:49,273 --> 00:12:51,106
LIM: You're pretty tough on my residents.

295
00:12:51,108 --> 00:12:52,441
Rebuking them in public,

296
00:12:52,443 --> 00:12:55,010
pimping them with questions
during surgery.

297
00:12:55,012 --> 00:12:56,645
Shame-based learning isn't my style.

298
00:12:56,647 --> 00:12:58,714
I'll bear that in mind.

299
00:12:58,716 --> 00:13:00,716
But this isn't about
my treatment of "the residents."

300
00:13:00,718 --> 00:13:02,384
You're concerned about Dr. Murphy.

301
00:13:02,386 --> 00:13:04,920
Well, a lot of doctors have
less than ideal bedside manner.

302
00:13:04,922 --> 00:13:06,755
- He's young...
- Would you ever have said

303
00:13:06,757 --> 00:13:08,824
something like that
to a patient as a resident?

304
00:13:08,826 --> 00:13:10,459
As a med student?

305
00:13:10,461 --> 00:13:11,593
And Murphy doesn't even understand

306
00:13:11,595 --> 00:13:12,895
he did anything wrong.

307
00:13:12,897 --> 00:13:14,363
Shaun has hard-wired differences

308
00:13:14,365 --> 00:13:16,531
- in the way he perceives things.
- Exactly.

309
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:17,733
No matter how hard he works,

310
00:13:17,735 --> 00:13:20,502
no matter how hard you try and help him,

311
00:13:20,504 --> 00:13:23,104
his limitations are not going to change.

312
00:13:23,106 --> 00:13:26,441
He's going to continue to
inflict them on our patients...

313
00:13:26,443 --> 00:13:29,143
all in the name of diversity
and inclusion.

314
00:13:31,682 --> 00:13:33,415
Shaun deserves to be here.

315
00:13:34,551 --> 00:13:37,619
Once you see what he's
capable of, you'll agree.

316
00:13:37,621 --> 00:13:39,386
I look forward to being proven wrong.

317
00:13:39,388 --> 00:13:40,471
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

318
00:13:40,473 --> 00:13:42,691
[ELEVATOR DOORS OPEN]

319
00:13:45,016 --> 00:13:46,795
Stay seated for 20 minutes.

320
00:13:46,797 --> 00:13:48,323
Don't want you passing out in the lobby.

321
00:13:48,325 --> 00:13:49,963
I know, I know. Thank you.

322
00:13:55,318 --> 00:13:57,070
This disease changed my relationships,

323
00:13:57,072 --> 00:13:59,874
changed my priorities, changed...

324
00:13:59,876 --> 00:14:01,241
who I am.

325
00:14:01,243 --> 00:14:02,574
Cancer is an identity.

326
00:14:02,576 --> 00:14:04,712
Cancer is cellular mutation.

327
00:14:04,714 --> 00:14:06,881
The people in this room are my people.

328
00:14:06,883 --> 00:14:09,983
What are you... 20 years old?
I'm triple your age.

329
00:14:09,985 --> 00:14:11,285
I don't think you're my "people."

330
00:14:11,287 --> 00:14:13,533
The last time I hung out with
my law-school friends...

331
00:14:13,535 --> 00:14:14,523
epic fail.

332
00:14:14,548 --> 00:14:16,413
The fact that you use
the phrase "epic fail,"

333
00:14:16,415 --> 00:14:17,558
kind of case in point.

334
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,460
They're all focused on what firm
they're gonna land at,

335
00:14:19,462 --> 00:14:21,562
and I'm all about whether...

336
00:14:21,564 --> 00:14:23,330
Candice's leukemia is responding

337
00:14:23,332 --> 00:14:25,032
to her new chemo regimen.

338
00:14:25,034 --> 00:14:26,599
By the way, she has this peppermint oil

339
00:14:26,601 --> 00:14:28,393
that is great for headaches.

340
00:14:32,741 --> 00:14:34,874
Ooh, I know that look.

341
00:14:34,876 --> 00:14:36,317
Here, here.

342
00:14:37,212 --> 00:14:38,778
[VOMITING]

343
00:14:38,780 --> 00:14:41,748
[COUGHING]

344
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,583
Got you, brother...

345
00:14:43,585 --> 00:14:45,052
whether you like it or not.

346
00:14:45,054 --> 00:14:46,619
[CHUCKLES]

347
00:14:49,458 --> 00:14:51,358
Show me where we are.

348
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:54,127
That angle runs pretty close
to the sacral nerve roots.

349
00:14:55,697 --> 00:14:57,063
How are we doing?

350
00:14:57,065 --> 00:14:58,497
MELENDEZ: Tumor's abutting
the iliac artery.

351
00:14:58,499 --> 00:15:00,299
I'm trying not to disrupt
the entire blood supply

352
00:15:00,301 --> 00:15:01,600
to his lower body.

353
00:15:01,602 --> 00:15:03,302
Dr. Han, I'm Morgan Reznick.

354
00:15:03,304 --> 00:15:05,604
I really enjoyed your article on Myotomy

355
00:15:05,606 --> 00:15:08,641
for infantile hypertrophic
pyloric stenosis.

356
00:15:09,444 --> 00:15:12,578
I appreciate the thorough
research behind your sucking up.

357
00:15:12,580 --> 00:15:14,380
And you are?

358
00:15:14,382 --> 00:15:15,848
Alex Park.

359
00:15:15,850 --> 00:15:18,317
Park... you were a cop.

360
00:15:18,319 --> 00:15:20,919
Medicine as a second career...
good stuff.

361
00:15:20,921 --> 00:15:22,989
Tends to bring a fresh perspective.

362
00:15:24,158 --> 00:15:25,591
[ALARM BEEPING RAPIDLY]

363
00:15:25,593 --> 00:15:28,127
I hit an artery. Take the needle.

364
00:15:28,129 --> 00:15:29,294
Blood's pooling in the pelvis.

365
00:15:29,296 --> 00:15:30,958
- Should we open him up?
- No.

366
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:32,530
Prep the femoral artery.
Get me an art cath set.

367
00:15:32,532 --> 00:15:34,550
- Pressure's dropping.
- Platinum coil.

368
00:15:34,552 --> 00:15:36,968
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

369
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:43,718
- [BEEPING STOPS]
- Nice save.

370
00:15:44,344 --> 00:15:45,943
Next time, don't hit the vessel.

371
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:49,614
There is no next time.

372
00:15:49,616 --> 00:15:51,449
The biopsy's too dangerous.

373
00:15:54,888 --> 00:15:57,188
[SIGHS]

374
00:15:57,190 --> 00:16:00,558
MELENDEZ: It is likely that it's
a benign notochord cell tumor.

375
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:02,343
They look like chordomas,

376
00:16:02,345 --> 00:16:03,828
but they're harmless and way more common.

377
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:05,162
But you don't know.

378
00:16:05,164 --> 00:16:07,231
Since we can't do the biopsy, no.

379
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,286
This is the problem with broad testing.

380
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:12,637
Everyone has abnormalities.

381
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:14,171
Most of them are nothing.

382
00:16:14,173 --> 00:16:15,840
But when we do find them,

383
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:17,942
we have to make some tough choices.

384
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:22,212
So, what exactly is my tough choice?

385
00:16:23,841 --> 00:16:25,516
We could remove the tumor.

386
00:16:25,518 --> 00:16:27,151
This is a very risky surgery.

387
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:29,353
There's a chance of paralysis or worse...

388
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:31,140
you may not make it off the table.

389
00:16:31,724 --> 00:16:33,434
Or you do nothing.

390
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,360
We'd continue to monitor it,

391
00:16:35,362 --> 00:16:36,726
do imaging every few weeks.

392
00:16:36,728 --> 00:16:38,828
But chordomas move very quickly.

393
00:16:38,830 --> 00:16:40,931
By the time any change
showed up on imaging,

394
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,433
it's most likely metastasized
throughout your body.

395
00:16:45,537 --> 00:16:49,039
So it probably isn't cancer,

396
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:52,576
but if it is and I wait, then I'll die.

397
00:16:52,578 --> 00:16:54,044
That's true.

398
00:16:54,046 --> 00:16:57,948
And if I don't wait
and I get the surgery,

399
00:16:57,950 --> 00:16:59,849
then there's a good chance I'll die.

400
00:16:59,851 --> 00:17:00,951
Yes.

401
00:17:06,324 --> 00:17:08,491
I'm gonna need to think this over.

402
00:17:08,493 --> 00:17:16,065
♪♪

403
00:17:16,067 --> 00:17:21,571
♪♪

404
00:17:23,442 --> 00:17:27,577
This is the May
<i>Annals of Neonatal Surgery.</i>

405
00:17:27,579 --> 00:17:30,779
I just finished March.
I need to read April now.

406
00:17:30,781 --> 00:17:32,448
LIM: Oh, I have April, Shaun.

407
00:17:32,450 --> 00:17:34,016
No.

408
00:17:34,018 --> 00:17:36,210
No, you're supposed to be reading

409
00:17:36,212 --> 00:17:38,673
<i>New Approaches in Neonatal Surgery.</i>

410
00:17:38,675 --> 00:17:41,419
Claire has the<i> British Journal</i>
<i>of Neonatology...</i>

411
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,533
Shaun...

412
00:17:51,846 --> 00:17:54,802
I think maybe you should
be quiet around Han

413
00:17:54,804 --> 00:17:57,018
for a little while.

414
00:17:57,641 --> 00:18:00,074
But then how will I answer his questions?

415
00:18:01,897 --> 00:18:04,646
Direct questions, absolutely answer.

416
00:18:04,648 --> 00:18:06,914
Otherwise, outside of the O.R.,

417
00:18:06,916 --> 00:18:08,683
you should stay out of his way.

418
00:18:11,588 --> 00:18:14,189
If someone had convinced Shaun
to do that with Dr. Melendez,

419
00:18:14,191 --> 00:18:16,558
he would still be on suction.

420
00:18:19,029 --> 00:18:20,228
[BEEP]

421
00:18:20,230 --> 00:18:22,464
MAN ON P.A.: <i>Code blue... NICU, Bed 4.</i>

422
00:18:22,466 --> 00:18:25,133
<i>Code blue... NICU, Bed 4.</i>

423
00:18:25,135 --> 00:18:26,534
[DOOR OPENS]

424
00:18:26,536 --> 00:18:27,935
[ALARM BEEPING RAPIDLY]

425
00:18:27,937 --> 00:18:30,604
O2 SATs dropped and central
venous pressure shot up.

426
00:18:30,606 --> 00:18:32,239
The Pulmonary Artery Band is failing.

427
00:18:32,241 --> 00:18:34,275
- Eight of dopamine.
- Let's get a mask on her.

428
00:18:34,277 --> 00:18:36,577
She won't last much longer.
We need other options.

429
00:18:36,579 --> 00:18:38,345
I'll update the parents.

430
00:18:38,347 --> 00:18:39,981
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

431
00:18:39,983 --> 00:18:41,961
LIM: Let's get her
on full cardiac support.

432
00:18:41,963 --> 00:18:43,651
♪♪

433
00:18:43,653 --> 00:18:46,154
[MACHINE BEEPING]

434
00:18:46,156 --> 00:18:48,156
[RESPIRATOR HISSING]

435
00:18:48,158 --> 00:18:54,261
♪♪

436
00:18:57,028 --> 00:18:59,134
What have you got? Anything?

437
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,079
This Cleveland group

438
00:19:01,081 --> 00:19:03,715
repaired a bowel protrusion
using enterolysis.

439
00:19:03,717 --> 00:19:06,251
I could cut out this excess
inflammatory tissue

440
00:19:06,253 --> 00:19:07,717
and segment of bowel atresia.

441
00:19:07,719 --> 00:19:09,829
Might make her intestines
small enough to fit.

442
00:19:09,831 --> 00:19:11,089
Promising.

443
00:19:11,091 --> 00:19:12,691
Given the size of her abdomen,

444
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:14,059
I need to remove a lot of bowel.

445
00:19:14,061 --> 00:19:16,562
There's a good chance she
wouldn't be able to absorb food.

446
00:19:16,564 --> 00:19:18,319
We'll have to find the right balance.

447
00:19:18,319 --> 00:19:20,285
It's our only workable plan.

448
00:19:20,287 --> 00:19:22,253
Best bet on the heart is
to cut through the ventricle,

449
00:19:22,255 --> 00:19:24,055
like Murphy suggested.

450
00:19:24,057 --> 00:19:26,891
Uh, you were concerned about
the suture line holding.

451
00:19:26,893 --> 00:19:28,493
Well, I still am.

452
00:19:28,495 --> 00:19:30,761
Hopefully, horizontal
mattress sutures will work.

453
00:19:30,763 --> 00:19:32,097
They should be able
to withstand the tension

454
00:19:32,099 --> 00:19:33,598
at the suture line.

455
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:35,900
[FADING] There's still
a risk of an aneurysm forming

456
00:19:35,902 --> 00:19:37,935
in the tissue underneath.

457
00:19:37,937 --> 00:19:40,771
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

458
00:19:40,773 --> 00:19:42,456
Dr. Lim?

459
00:19:42,876 --> 00:19:45,210
I have an idea I'd like to share,

460
00:19:45,212 --> 00:19:47,879
even though Dr. Han
didn't ask me a question.

461
00:19:52,085 --> 00:19:54,151
Yeah, go ahead, Shaun.

462
00:19:54,153 --> 00:19:56,020
If we go in through the atrium,

463
00:19:56,022 --> 00:19:57,854
we wouldn't have to worry
about the suture line...

464
00:19:57,856 --> 00:19:59,689
It's the same issue we discussed.

465
00:19:59,691 --> 00:20:01,691
There's not enough room
inside the baby's heart

466
00:20:01,693 --> 00:20:03,193
to stitch the patches in the place.

467
00:20:03,195 --> 00:20:05,695
Oh, we don't need to, Dr. Han.

468
00:20:05,697 --> 00:20:08,198
We can make a plug
small enough for her heart...

469
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,600
a PTFE disc with a stem like a mushroom.

470
00:20:10,602 --> 00:20:12,403
Then we can insert the stem
through one of the holes

471
00:20:12,405 --> 00:20:14,104
until the disc presses against the wall,

472
00:20:14,106 --> 00:20:15,656
covering all the holes.

473
00:20:16,575 --> 00:20:20,444
L-Like a stopper in a bathtub.

474
00:20:20,446 --> 00:20:21,711
Yes.

475
00:20:21,713 --> 00:20:23,580
The higher pressure on
the left side of her heart

476
00:20:23,582 --> 00:20:24,948
would keep it in place.

477
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:26,883
We wouldn't even need to stitch.

478
00:20:28,421 --> 00:20:30,353
Great idea.

479
00:20:30,355 --> 00:20:32,088
We should take this to the parents.

480
00:20:32,090 --> 00:20:33,889
Great idea for the heart.

481
00:20:33,891 --> 00:20:36,459
But we need to tell them that
our current plan

482
00:20:36,461 --> 00:20:37,493
for the abdominal repair

483
00:20:37,495 --> 00:20:39,929
is considerably more of a long shot.

484
00:20:39,931 --> 00:20:42,516
And that fixing the heart
takes an option off the table.

485
00:20:43,368 --> 00:20:45,234
Withdrawing care.

486
00:20:54,645 --> 00:20:56,447
LARRY: You can't move that card.

487
00:20:56,948 --> 00:20:58,414
Excuse me?

488
00:20:58,416 --> 00:20:59,615
Who cheats at solitaire?

489
00:20:59,617 --> 00:21:01,184
You're literally only cheating yourself.

490
00:21:01,186 --> 00:21:02,552
Again.

491
00:21:02,554 --> 00:21:03,919
Good morning, Larry.

492
00:21:03,921 --> 00:21:05,754
Is it a macho thing?

493
00:21:05,756 --> 00:21:07,522
Like a real man should
be able to make it through

494
00:21:07,524 --> 00:21:10,025
without leaning on a label
or the people who go with it?

495
00:21:12,129 --> 00:21:14,096
Embracing cancer as an identity

496
00:21:14,098 --> 00:21:16,364
is the last thing
any one of us should be doing.

497
00:21:16,366 --> 00:21:19,534
It underscores everything
horrible right now.

498
00:21:20,437 --> 00:21:22,370
We're in a daily battle for our lives.

499
00:21:22,372 --> 00:21:24,573
I see no value in dwelling on that.

500
00:21:28,946 --> 00:21:30,512
Candice is late.

501
00:21:31,816 --> 00:21:34,182
Which means either her niece
forgot to pick her up.

502
00:21:34,184 --> 00:21:36,278
Again.

503
00:21:36,821 --> 00:21:38,697
Or she got some bad news.

504
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:41,256
Or she's already dead.

505
00:21:43,494 --> 00:21:46,261
- [OBJECT THUDS, BAG ZIPS]
- We<i> are</i> in a daily battle.

506
00:21:49,166 --> 00:21:51,454
I'd rather have some company.

507
00:21:51,456 --> 00:21:59,107
♪♪

508
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:07,215
♪♪

509
00:22:07,217 --> 00:22:09,117
I spoke to my mother and brother,

510
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:11,730
and they both think
I shouldn't do the surgery.

511
00:22:12,389 --> 00:22:14,322
Apparently they're more scared
of your surgical skills

512
00:22:14,324 --> 00:22:15,985
than they are of this tumor.

513
00:22:17,194 --> 00:22:19,093
And where do you stand?

514
00:22:19,095 --> 00:22:21,062
I need numbers.

515
00:22:21,064 --> 00:22:22,363
Please.

516
00:22:22,365 --> 00:22:25,867
♪♪

517
00:22:25,869 --> 00:22:28,872
The stats on something like this, it...

518
00:22:29,472 --> 00:22:30,738
there are a lot of variables.

519
00:22:30,740 --> 00:22:32,807
What are the odds
I make it through the surgery

520
00:22:32,809 --> 00:22:35,129
without any complications?

521
00:22:35,745 --> 00:22:37,945
It's a challenging procedure.

522
00:22:37,947 --> 00:22:40,782
Zero complications, I'd say 80%.

523
00:22:42,351 --> 00:22:45,452
But it is very unlikely
this tumor is malignant.

524
00:22:45,454 --> 00:22:47,182
Give me a number.

525
00:22:47,924 --> 00:22:50,558
About 5% chance it's a chordoma.

526
00:22:57,900 --> 00:23:00,067
The numbers agree with your family.

527
00:23:00,069 --> 00:23:01,569
So do I.

528
00:23:05,708 --> 00:23:07,808
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

529
00:23:10,313 --> 00:23:11,878
I've always been
more comfortable with action

530
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:13,447
than inaction.

531
00:23:16,885 --> 00:23:19,286
I want you to do the surgery.

532
00:23:21,490 --> 00:23:22,656
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

533
00:23:22,658 --> 00:23:24,786
Certainty comes at a price.

534
00:23:24,788 --> 00:23:33,533
♪♪

535
00:23:33,535 --> 00:23:36,369
DIANE: She'll be able to get off
the life support machines?

536
00:23:36,371 --> 00:23:38,238
HAN: If everything goes well, yes.

537
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:39,972
She'll have a strong heart.

538
00:23:39,974 --> 00:23:41,807
How soon can you do it?

539
00:23:43,478 --> 00:23:45,144
You should know we feel less confident

540
00:23:45,146 --> 00:23:47,201
about our plan for her bowel.

541
00:23:47,582 --> 00:23:50,316
The chance of failure is quite high.

542
00:23:50,318 --> 00:23:51,784
How high?

543
00:23:51,786 --> 00:23:54,721
LIM: I put it at 90%
that the repair won't work.

544
00:23:54,723 --> 00:23:57,823
Which would lead
to irreversible malnutrition.

545
00:23:57,825 --> 00:24:01,340
Your daughter would slowly
starve to death over months.

546
00:24:02,029 --> 00:24:04,130
Right now, her body is working very hard

547
00:24:04,132 --> 00:24:05,397
just to stay alive.

548
00:24:05,399 --> 00:24:08,700
♪♪

549
00:24:08,702 --> 00:24:11,003
If we were to turn off the machines...

550
00:24:11,005 --> 00:24:12,958
Turn off the machines?

551
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:15,741
♪♪

552
00:24:15,743 --> 00:24:18,816
...she would pass quickly.
And peacefully.

553
00:24:19,346 --> 00:24:21,680
If the heart surgery is a success,

554
00:24:21,682 --> 00:24:23,783
that won't be an option.

555
00:24:23,785 --> 00:24:25,617
Oh. [BREATHES DEEPLY]

556
00:24:25,619 --> 00:24:27,519
Why not try to fix the bowel first

557
00:24:27,521 --> 00:24:28,720
to see if it works?

558
00:24:28,722 --> 00:24:30,522
We won't know if the bowel is viable

559
00:24:30,524 --> 00:24:32,258
until after the heart is.

560
00:24:33,460 --> 00:24:35,874
We have to do the surgery.

561
00:24:36,229 --> 00:24:38,530
But if this doesn't work,
she could starve to death.

562
00:24:38,532 --> 00:24:41,433
- It's worth the risk...
- It's not our risk. It's<i> hers.</i>

563
00:24:41,435 --> 00:24:44,803
So, instead, you're ready
to give up on our daughter?

564
00:24:44,805 --> 00:24:47,339
I mean, it's like we're
right back at the ultrasound.

565
00:24:47,341 --> 00:24:49,941
We decided together
to continue this pregnancy.

566
00:24:49,943 --> 00:24:51,910
So this is as much
my fault as it is yours.

567
00:24:51,912 --> 00:24:53,312
My fault?

568
00:24:53,314 --> 00:24:55,280
Because of the medication?

569
00:24:56,917 --> 00:25:00,315
I cannot turn off that machine.

570
00:25:01,021 --> 00:25:03,855
Your guilt is stopping you from
admitting what we need to do.

571
00:25:03,857 --> 00:25:06,490
My guilt has nothing to do with this.

572
00:25:06,492 --> 00:25:09,227
- I am fighting for my daughter.
- So am I.

573
00:25:11,675 --> 00:25:13,676
Since the parents can't agree,
the decision

574
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:15,960
about the baby's care
will be made by a judge

575
00:25:15,962 --> 00:25:17,814
who will rely on our recommendation.

576
00:25:18,399 --> 00:25:20,032
So we make the choice,

577
00:25:20,034 --> 00:25:21,600
but the parents live with it?

578
00:25:24,131 --> 00:25:25,804
Well, maybe that's a good thing.

579
00:25:27,474 --> 00:25:29,507
For parents to have to decide between

580
00:25:29,509 --> 00:25:31,243
letting their daughter die

581
00:25:31,245 --> 00:25:34,980
or fighting for her life,
knowing she may suffer horribly,

582
00:25:34,982 --> 00:25:37,477
maybe it's better
if we carry that burden.

583
00:25:40,221 --> 00:25:41,820
Dr. Lim?

584
00:25:41,822 --> 00:25:43,322
Your decision would be?

585
00:25:44,791 --> 00:25:46,491
Take her off life support.

586
00:25:46,493 --> 00:25:48,660
The odds are stacked against
the bowel repair working.

587
00:25:48,662 --> 00:25:51,696
Those numbers reflect the
general population of doctors.

588
00:25:51,698 --> 00:25:54,102
I think Dr. Lim and I
are better than that.

589
00:25:54,703 --> 00:25:56,163
We can beat the odds.

590
00:26:03,921 --> 00:26:05,562
One of the things I'm not going to miss

591
00:26:05,564 --> 00:26:07,245
about being Chief of Surgery

592
00:26:07,247 --> 00:26:10,135
is being responsible
for choices like this.

593
00:26:12,852 --> 00:26:15,219
Dr. Han, it's your department...

594
00:26:15,221 --> 00:26:16,888
it's your call.

595
00:26:22,962 --> 00:26:24,428
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

596
00:26:24,430 --> 00:26:26,230
GLASSMAN: You've been here all night?

597
00:26:26,735 --> 00:26:28,165
I've been working on a case

598
00:26:28,167 --> 00:26:30,768
with the new Chief of Surgery, Dr. Han.

599
00:26:30,770 --> 00:26:33,388
- How's that going?
- Not very well.

600
00:26:33,390 --> 00:26:35,405
He plays music in the operating room.

601
00:26:35,407 --> 00:26:36,889
Oh, geez. One of those.

602
00:26:36,891 --> 00:26:38,191
And he says I need to focus on

603
00:26:38,193 --> 00:26:40,290
our patients' emotional needs.

604
00:26:40,745 --> 00:26:42,845
Well, that's a tough assignment for you.

605
00:26:43,708 --> 00:26:45,175
Mm.

606
00:26:49,466 --> 00:26:53,167
You ever wish you had, you know,

607
00:26:53,169 --> 00:26:55,892
friends, co-workers on the spectrum?

608
00:26:56,264 --> 00:26:57,860
Not usually.

609
00:26:57,862 --> 00:27:00,773
But maybe Dr. Han
wouldn't notice me as much

610
00:27:00,775 --> 00:27:03,105
if I weren't the only doctor with ASD.

611
00:27:06,204 --> 00:27:08,103
There's this kid in chemo,

612
00:27:08,105 --> 00:27:11,288
just [CHUCKLES] obsessed
with having cancer.

613
00:27:11,315 --> 00:27:12,615
It's all he talks about.

614
00:27:12,617 --> 00:27:14,254
He wants to be friends
with everybody in the ward.

615
00:27:14,256 --> 00:27:15,926
That's very smart of him.

616
00:27:15,928 --> 00:27:19,121
Speigel et Al. showed
an increase in overall survival

617
00:27:19,123 --> 00:27:21,491
and quality of life measures
in breast cancer patients

618
00:27:21,493 --> 00:27:24,527
who formed social bonds with
others battling the disease.

619
00:27:25,430 --> 00:27:27,430
What should I do about Dr. Han?

620
00:27:29,901 --> 00:27:32,735
[EXHALES DEEPLY] I don't know. Um...

621
00:27:32,737 --> 00:27:34,404
just do your work,

622
00:27:34,406 --> 00:27:36,706
be a good surgeon,
be an excellent surgeon.

623
00:27:36,708 --> 00:27:38,941
Over time, he'll forget about the autism.

624
00:27:38,943 --> 00:27:40,342
Why would that happen?

625
00:27:40,344 --> 00:27:43,345
He'll see that you have
the skill, you have dedication.

626
00:27:43,347 --> 00:27:45,680
I have autism.

627
00:27:45,682 --> 00:27:47,449
It's part of who I am.

628
00:27:47,451 --> 00:27:49,451
[CONVERSATIONS CONTINUE]

629
00:27:54,358 --> 00:27:58,127
[RESPIRATOR HISSING, MONITOR BEEPING]

630
00:27:58,129 --> 00:27:59,761
The judge...?

631
00:27:59,763 --> 00:28:01,463
Accepted our recommendation

632
00:28:01,465 --> 00:28:03,373
and ruled in favor of surgery.

633
00:28:04,001 --> 00:28:05,479
Thank you, Doctor.

634
00:28:05,481 --> 00:28:09,604
♪♪

635
00:28:09,606 --> 00:28:11,040
[SIGHS]

636
00:28:11,042 --> 00:28:12,441
Okay, Percy.

637
00:28:12,443 --> 00:28:14,276
♪♪

638
00:28:14,278 --> 00:28:16,145
[VOICE BREAKING] Momma loves you.

639
00:28:16,147 --> 00:28:19,147
♪♪

640
00:28:19,149 --> 00:28:20,458
I love you, Percy.

641
00:28:20,460 --> 00:28:28,757
♪♪

642
00:28:28,759 --> 00:28:36,397
♪♪

643
00:28:36,399 --> 00:28:44,005
♪♪

644
00:28:44,007 --> 00:28:53,647
♪♪

645
00:28:55,995 --> 00:28:57,661
CLAIRE: Should we remove more bowel?

646
00:28:57,663 --> 00:28:58,863
That would take us to the ilium.

647
00:28:58,865 --> 00:29:01,032
She won't gain enough weight to thrive.

648
00:29:01,429 --> 00:29:03,128
Her abdominal muscles are tight

649
00:29:03,130 --> 00:29:05,393
from developing around an empty cavity.

650
00:29:06,100 --> 00:29:07,966
♪ But the days, girl,
just slip away, oh, yeah ♪

651
00:29:07,968 --> 00:29:10,635
They're cinched around
her tummy like a corset.

652
00:29:10,637 --> 00:29:12,037
What if we unbuttoned it?

653
00:29:12,039 --> 00:29:13,205
Released the muscle

654
00:29:13,207 --> 00:29:15,473
and increased the abdominal
circumference.

655
00:29:15,475 --> 00:29:16,782
Those muscles are part
of her abdominal wall.

656
00:29:16,807 --> 00:29:18,310
Not if we separate the layers...

657
00:29:18,312 --> 00:29:21,113
create a plane between
the skin and the muscle.

658
00:29:21,115 --> 00:29:22,948
♪♪

659
00:29:22,950 --> 00:29:24,817
You good if Murphy and I
start on the heart?

660
00:29:25,652 --> 00:29:28,220
Dr. Browne, you're with me
on the abdomen.

661
00:29:29,623 --> 00:29:30,923
Clearing the field.

662
00:29:30,925 --> 00:29:32,925
Han is on the call schedule next weekend.

663
00:29:32,927 --> 00:29:35,160
Maybe Carmen will switch with me
so I can cover with him?

664
00:29:35,162 --> 00:29:38,262
Or maybe you shouldn't try so hard.

665
00:29:38,264 --> 00:29:39,761
Retractor.

666
00:29:40,634 --> 00:29:42,567
Some of us don't have
a cool former career...

667
00:29:42,569 --> 00:29:44,235
or an easy-going, mellow demeanor.

668
00:29:44,237 --> 00:29:45,603
People are never gonna crowd in my corner

669
00:29:45,605 --> 00:29:46,871
because I'm just so likable.

670
00:29:46,873 --> 00:29:48,906
Well, you could try being nice to them.

671
00:29:48,908 --> 00:29:50,642
- Well, this is easier.
- There it is.

672
00:29:53,347 --> 00:29:55,046
Does it look like cancer?

673
00:29:55,048 --> 00:29:56,815
It's not labeled.

674
00:29:56,817 --> 00:29:59,155
We're all gonna have to wait
for the pathologist's report.

675
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:01,018
[MONITOR BEEPING]

676
00:30:01,020 --> 00:30:02,587
Probe.

677
00:30:02,589 --> 00:30:04,288
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

678
00:30:07,594 --> 00:30:09,227
The artery is in the way.

679
00:30:09,229 --> 00:30:11,529
We can't get at the tumor
without him bleeding out.

680
00:30:11,531 --> 00:30:16,467
♪♪

681
00:30:16,469 --> 00:30:17,969
We're gonna have
to take it from the back.

682
00:30:17,971 --> 00:30:21,072
- But the S1 nerve root...
- Is something he can live without.

683
00:30:21,074 --> 00:30:22,606
Dissecting scissors.

684
00:30:22,608 --> 00:30:26,510
♪♪

685
00:30:26,512 --> 00:30:27,912
HAN: Pledget anchor.

686
00:30:27,914 --> 00:30:30,514
♪ You'll be leaving me soon,
like hell you will ♪

687
00:30:30,516 --> 00:30:34,919
♪ The owl gazing at the moon ♪

688
00:30:34,921 --> 00:30:39,123
♪ Is the feeling that I get
when I'm lookin' at you ♪

689
00:30:39,125 --> 00:30:43,127
♪ The sun will rise and fade the stars ♪

690
00:30:43,129 --> 00:30:44,262
The plug is in position.

691
00:30:44,264 --> 00:30:46,244
You ready to test the bowel repair?

692
00:30:46,832 --> 00:30:47,998
♪ And you're leaving me soon,
like hell you are ♪

693
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,566
Let's take her off cardiac support.

694
00:30:49,568 --> 00:30:51,368
Dr. Murphy, it was your idea.

695
00:30:51,370 --> 00:30:52,969
You do the honors.

696
00:30:52,971 --> 00:30:58,208
♪♪

697
00:30:58,210 --> 00:30:59,510
[CLICKS]

698
00:30:59,512 --> 00:31:00,878
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

699
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:03,747
♪♪

700
00:31:03,749 --> 00:31:06,683
Abdominal pressure is normal.

701
00:31:06,685 --> 00:31:09,052
The intestines are perfusing.

702
00:31:09,054 --> 00:31:12,255
♪♪

703
00:31:12,257 --> 00:31:14,324
- [ALARM BEEPING RAPIDLY]
- HAN: Pulmonary pressure's spiking.

704
00:31:14,326 --> 00:31:15,526
Prostacyclin and nitric oxide...

705
00:31:15,528 --> 00:31:16,727
we need to get her lung pressure down.

706
00:31:16,729 --> 00:31:18,295
Oxygen SATs are dropping.

707
00:31:18,297 --> 00:31:20,563
No response to pulmonary vasodilators.

708
00:31:20,565 --> 00:31:23,299
Now the heart's too strong.
It's overpowering her lungs.

709
00:31:23,301 --> 00:31:25,367
She needs to go back on cardiac support.

710
00:31:25,369 --> 00:31:26,502
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

711
00:31:26,504 --> 00:31:28,504
[CLICKS, BEEPING STEADIES]

712
00:31:28,506 --> 00:31:33,643
♪♪

713
00:31:33,645 --> 00:31:37,045
Persephone won't starve to death...

714
00:31:37,615 --> 00:31:39,949
but she will drown in her own fluids.

715
00:31:39,951 --> 00:31:42,452
♪♪

716
00:31:42,454 --> 00:31:47,924
♪♪

717
00:31:47,926 --> 00:31:54,663
♪♪

718
00:31:54,665 --> 00:31:56,197
I'll talk to the parents.

719
00:31:56,199 --> 00:31:57,566
May I come?

720
00:31:57,568 --> 00:32:03,404
♪♪

721
00:32:03,406 --> 00:32:09,110
♪♪

722
00:32:09,112 --> 00:32:11,713
Now that Persephone's heart
is pumping at full power,

723
00:32:11,715 --> 00:32:13,448
her lungs are overwhelmed.

724
00:32:15,185 --> 00:32:16,885
The humane thing to do

725
00:32:16,887 --> 00:32:19,554
is to turn off the machines
and let her go.

726
00:32:20,724 --> 00:32:22,632
No, I-I can't...

727
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:24,493
I can't give up on her.
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

728
00:32:24,495 --> 00:32:27,562
♪♪

729
00:32:27,564 --> 00:32:29,389
Because you fought for her

730
00:32:30,366 --> 00:32:32,633
every minute since she was born.

731
00:32:32,635 --> 00:32:34,935
Before that, when you were
taking your medication

732
00:32:34,937 --> 00:32:36,069
for the depression,

733
00:32:36,071 --> 00:32:37,897
you were fighting to keep going

734
00:32:38,407 --> 00:32:40,140
so you could bring her into the world.

735
00:32:40,142 --> 00:32:42,510
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

736
00:32:42,512 --> 00:32:46,580
♪♪

737
00:32:46,582 --> 00:32:56,456
♪♪

738
00:32:56,458 --> 00:32:59,527
But letting go of Percy
is not giving up on her.

739
00:32:59,529 --> 00:33:01,595
♪♪

740
00:33:01,597 --> 00:33:04,397
It's listening to what
her body is telling us.

741
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:09,201
♪♪

742
00:33:09,203 --> 00:33:10,537
She's hit her limit.

743
00:33:10,539 --> 00:33:14,440
♪♪

744
00:33:14,442 --> 00:33:16,009
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

745
00:33:16,011 --> 00:33:23,783
♪♪

746
00:33:23,785 --> 00:33:27,787
♪♪

747
00:33:27,789 --> 00:33:29,622
Okay.

748
00:33:29,624 --> 00:33:39,297
♪♪

749
00:33:39,299 --> 00:33:45,571
♪♪

750
00:33:45,573 --> 00:33:48,006
♪♪

751
00:33:48,008 --> 00:33:49,741
[SOBS]

752
00:33:49,743 --> 00:33:53,178
♪♪

753
00:33:53,180 --> 00:33:54,680
[CRYING]

754
00:33:54,682 --> 00:33:58,116
♪♪

755
00:34:00,633 --> 00:34:02,901
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

756
00:34:03,875 --> 00:34:05,708
HAN: I want Persephone to look
as good as possible

757
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:07,243
for the parents.

758
00:34:07,245 --> 00:34:10,547
♪♪

759
00:34:10,549 --> 00:34:12,214
[SIGHS]

760
00:34:12,216 --> 00:34:14,149
Let's turn off cardiac support.

761
00:34:14,151 --> 00:34:16,518
♪♪

762
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:19,254
[CLICKS, BEEPING]

763
00:34:19,256 --> 00:34:20,823
Ventilator.

764
00:34:20,825 --> 00:34:22,223
♪♪

765
00:34:22,225 --> 00:34:23,792
Let's take a minute.

766
00:34:23,794 --> 00:34:26,194
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

767
00:34:26,196 --> 00:34:33,602
♪♪

768
00:34:33,604 --> 00:34:42,110
♪♪

769
00:34:42,112 --> 00:34:48,916
♪♪

770
00:34:48,918 --> 00:34:52,187
[LOUD, RHYTHMIC BEEPING]

771
00:34:52,189 --> 00:34:53,621
♪♪

772
00:34:53,623 --> 00:35:00,362
♪♪

773
00:35:00,364 --> 00:35:07,102
♪♪

774
00:35:07,104 --> 00:35:08,769
Check valve.

775
00:35:08,771 --> 00:35:13,108
♪♪

776
00:35:13,110 --> 00:35:15,543
Every time the heart contracted,

777
00:35:15,545 --> 00:35:17,778
blood went into the opposite
side of the heart

778
00:35:17,780 --> 00:35:19,680
and raised lung pressure.

779
00:35:19,682 --> 00:35:22,416
The hole reduced the pressure
when it got too high

780
00:35:22,418 --> 00:35:23,817
because it allowed backflow.

781
00:35:23,819 --> 00:35:27,254
But our repair of the defect
blocked this backwards flow.

782
00:35:27,256 --> 00:35:29,656
What if we made it so
she still had a heart defect,

783
00:35:29,658 --> 00:35:31,558
but only when she needed it?

784
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:35,529
It'd be like an unlatched door
in the wall of the heart.

785
00:35:35,531 --> 00:35:37,731
When the pressure gets too high
on the right side,

786
00:35:37,733 --> 00:35:40,600
the door swings open, releasing
the pressure on the lungs.

787
00:35:40,602 --> 00:35:42,503
The rest of the time, it stays shut.

788
00:35:42,505 --> 00:35:45,372
It should reduce lung pressure
by a third. Is that enough?

789
00:35:45,374 --> 00:35:46,507
It depends on how high

790
00:35:46,509 --> 00:35:48,509
her pulmonary vascular resistance is.

791
00:35:48,511 --> 00:35:50,877
PVR is pulmonary artery pressure

792
00:35:50,879 --> 00:35:53,980
minus wedge pressure divided
by cardiac output times 80.

793
00:35:53,982 --> 00:35:59,419
♪♪

794
00:35:59,421 --> 00:36:04,844
♪♪

795
00:36:04,846 --> 00:36:06,725
CANDICE: The last time I saw my doctor,

796
00:36:06,727 --> 00:36:09,628
he told me I had six months to live.

797
00:36:09,630 --> 00:36:11,431
He also told me I should
marry an accountant

798
00:36:11,433 --> 00:36:12,765
and move to North Dakota.

799
00:36:12,767 --> 00:36:14,367
LARRY: You don't say.

800
00:36:14,369 --> 00:36:16,869
When I asked if it would
help my cancer, he said no,

801
00:36:16,871 --> 00:36:19,672
just make the six months
seem much longer.

802
00:36:19,674 --> 00:36:22,275
[BOTH LAUGH]

803
00:36:23,010 --> 00:36:26,679
What's the difference between
a Neo-Nazi and cancer?

804
00:36:26,681 --> 00:36:28,274
Cancer doesn't discriminate.

805
00:36:28,276 --> 00:36:29,515
[LAUGHS]

806
00:36:29,517 --> 00:36:31,517
[LAUGHS]

807
00:36:31,519 --> 00:36:33,285
I knew a guy once...

808
00:36:33,287 --> 00:36:35,720
his Zodiac sign was Cancer.

809
00:36:35,722 --> 00:36:38,890
It was really ironic how he died.

810
00:36:40,260 --> 00:36:42,027
Uh, uh, how's that?

811
00:36:42,029 --> 00:36:43,962
He was eaten by a giant crab.

812
00:36:43,964 --> 00:36:47,832
[LAUGHTER]
- Oh, geez.

813
00:36:47,834 --> 00:36:49,267
[LAUGHS]

814
00:36:49,269 --> 00:36:51,503
Aaron, glioma.

815
00:36:51,505 --> 00:36:54,038
Candice, leukemia.

816
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:55,307
Gin rummy or blackjack?

817
00:36:55,309 --> 00:36:57,342
How fast do you want to take my money?

818
00:36:57,344 --> 00:36:58,843
Blackjack.

819
00:36:58,845 --> 00:37:00,326
Cut 'em.

820
00:37:12,243 --> 00:37:14,310
Did you get it all?

821
00:37:17,396 --> 00:37:18,829
Yes...

822
00:37:18,831 --> 00:37:20,764
totally clear margins.

823
00:37:20,766 --> 00:37:22,433
But the only way to achieve that

824
00:37:22,435 --> 00:37:24,935
involved removing the nerve
that controls your left foot.

825
00:37:26,572 --> 00:37:29,873
Rehab and an advanced orthotic may help,

826
00:37:29,875 --> 00:37:32,676
but you will walk with a limp.

827
00:37:32,678 --> 00:37:34,978
Final pathology will let us know
if it was worth it.

828
00:37:39,157 --> 00:37:40,984
I'll let you know when it comes in.

829
00:37:43,215 --> 00:37:45,481
It doesn't matter anymore.

830
00:37:48,412 --> 00:37:50,645
It's not like you can
put the tumor back in.

831
00:37:58,303 --> 00:38:00,570
[BABY CRYING]

832
00:38:05,777 --> 00:38:08,344
Is she... okay?

833
00:38:09,447 --> 00:38:13,683
She still has a surgery or two
in her future, but, yes.

834
00:38:13,685 --> 00:38:15,276
She's gonna be great.

835
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:18,887
- [BREATHES SHARPLY]
- [SNIFFLES]

836
00:38:18,889 --> 00:38:20,422
Can I hold her?

837
00:38:20,424 --> 00:38:22,617
I think that would be very nice.

838
00:38:23,227 --> 00:38:25,093
For both of you.

839
00:38:25,095 --> 00:38:34,069
♪♪

840
00:38:34,071 --> 00:38:35,904
[BABY CRYING]

841
00:38:35,906 --> 00:38:40,008
♪♪

842
00:38:40,010 --> 00:38:42,377
[CRYING] Hi, angel.

843
00:38:42,379 --> 00:38:43,278
♪♪

844
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:44,413
[BABY COOS]

845
00:38:44,415 --> 00:38:47,249
Oh, my baby. [SMOOCHES]

846
00:38:47,251 --> 00:38:50,485
♪♪

847
00:38:50,487 --> 00:38:52,019
Come hold her.

848
00:38:52,021 --> 00:38:58,426
♪♪

849
00:38:58,428 --> 00:39:00,928
You were fighting for her, too.

850
00:39:00,930 --> 00:39:04,131
♪♪

851
00:39:04,133 --> 00:39:06,133
[SNIFFLES]

852
00:39:06,135 --> 00:39:08,569
- [BOTH CHUCKLE]
- She's beautiful.

853
00:39:08,571 --> 00:39:15,710
♪♪

854
00:39:15,712 --> 00:39:17,296
Nice work.

855
00:39:18,514 --> 00:39:20,132
Thank you.

856
00:39:21,050 --> 00:39:23,917
- [BABY CRYING]
- She's beautiful.

857
00:39:23,919 --> 00:39:25,486
Listen to her. Oh.

858
00:39:25,488 --> 00:39:28,122
[CRYING]

859
00:39:28,124 --> 00:39:35,262
♪♪

860
00:39:36,866 --> 00:39:38,398
Thank you.

861
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:41,568
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

862
00:39:43,538 --> 00:39:45,705
Minesh's biopsy results?

863
00:39:50,512 --> 00:39:52,980
[SIGHS]

864
00:39:55,751 --> 00:39:57,050
You don't want to know
if we wasted our time

865
00:39:57,052 --> 00:39:58,462
almost killing him?

866
00:39:59,621 --> 00:40:01,488
Can't put the tumor back.

867
00:40:17,506 --> 00:40:19,692
Hello, Dr. Han.

868
00:40:20,208 --> 00:40:22,442
You take the bus, too?

869
00:40:22,444 --> 00:40:23,843
No, Shaun.

870
00:40:23,845 --> 00:40:26,282
I just wanted to talk to you.

871
00:40:26,948 --> 00:40:29,015
[INHALES SHARPLY]

872
00:40:29,017 --> 00:40:33,218
You really do have
remarkable diagnostic skills.

873
00:40:33,220 --> 00:40:36,188
I have to admit, you're an
asset to this hospital.

874
00:40:36,626 --> 00:40:38,390
Yes, I am.

875
00:40:41,061 --> 00:40:44,383
I spoke to the Residency
Director of Pathology.

876
00:40:45,032 --> 00:40:48,012
And we both agree
you'll be a great fit there.

877
00:40:50,438 --> 00:40:53,706
I'm a surgical resident.

878
00:40:53,708 --> 00:40:55,808
As a pathology resident,

879
00:40:55,810 --> 00:40:58,677
you'll touch cases and lives

880
00:40:58,679 --> 00:41:02,247
across all the medical departments.

881
00:41:02,249 --> 00:41:04,483
It's an opportunity
for you to help patients

882
00:41:04,485 --> 00:41:07,490
without having to deal with patients.

883
00:41:08,616 --> 00:41:12,457
Given your difficulties with
communication and social cues,

884
00:41:12,459 --> 00:41:14,955
I think it will be a much better fit.

885
00:41:15,795 --> 00:41:17,458
No, thank you.

886
00:41:18,292 --> 00:41:21,198
I have been working very hard

887
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:24,006
at my communication skills.

888
00:41:24,571 --> 00:41:26,759
Hard work isn't enough.

889
00:41:27,507 --> 00:41:29,273
You have to do the job.

890
00:41:31,811 --> 00:41:36,080
I am a surgical resident.

891
00:41:37,884 --> 00:41:39,522
You were.

892
00:41:40,787 --> 00:41:43,520
And you're gonna do
great work in pathology.

893
00:41:45,358 --> 00:41:48,859
